SUMMARY:"That One Day Women Will Be Treated and Thought of the Same Way as Men"
DESCRIPTION:On Sunday\, April 12\, Historic Rock Ford’s Untold Stories of the Revolution Lecture Series welcomes Mickey Herr as she presents\, “That One Day Women Will Be Treated and Thought of the Same Way as Men: Considering Women’s Contributions to Colonial Pennsylvania.”  \n\n\n\nHerr will share highlights from her research into Colonial Pennsylvania women\, a process of discovery which caused her to rethink everything she thought she knew. She found ministers\, interpreters\, diarists\, an inventor\, a fur trader\, and more! This revelation became the catalyst for a project of the National Society of the Colonial Dames of America in The Commonwealth of Pennsylvania\, “For the Common Good: The Women Who Shaped Our Nation\,” a nine-part docuseries featuring women who made important contributions to the founding of America. Mickey will highlight Lancaster-area ladies\, including Ann Wood Henry\, the first woman to hold public office in Pennsylvania.  \n\n\n\nThis presentation will begin at 2 PM in the Langmuir Education Room located on the first floor of the Rock Ford Barn. Prior to the lecture\, attendees may visit the Snyder Gallery and our 2026 Focus Exhibit. The Snyder Gallery closes at 4 PM.
URL:https://visitlancastercity.com/event/that-one-day-women-will-be-treated-and-thought-of-the-same-way-as-men/
LOCATION:Historic Rock Ford\, 881 Rockford Road\, Lancaster\, PA\, 17602\, United States
CATEGORIES:History
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitlancastercity.com/wp-content/uploads/Untold-Womens-Contributions-in-Colonial-PA.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Historic Rock Ford":MAILTO:office@HistoricRockFord.org
END:VEVENT
