SUMMARY:Earth Day Yoga at Gallery Grow
DESCRIPTION:A gentle\, beginner-friendly Earth Day yoga class focused on breath\, movement\, and reconnecting with nature. \n\n\n\nJoin yoga teacher Maggie Mowery for an hour-long yoga class inspired by Earth Day and the idea that spending time with plants and green spaces can be an important part of your wellness journey. This grounding session will include breath awareness\, gentle movement\, and a guided meditation. Maggie is an E-RYT 200 certified yoga teacher with over eight years of teaching experience and specializes in beginner-friendly\, accessible\, alignment-based yoga. This class is well suited for those new to yoga as well as seasoned yogis looking for a mindful\, nurturing practice. \n\n\n\nWhen she’s not on the mat\, Maggie loves to paint\, sculpt in clay\, spend time in nature or her garden\, and be with loved ones. She and her partner also regularly volunteer at Lancaster Farm Sanctuary in Mount Joy\, PA. \n\n\n\nAfter the session\, attendees are invited to shop and enjoy an exclusive 20% off before 12pm. Please note that this class will be held upstairs in our Loft area and is accessible by stairs only.
URL:https://visitlancastercity.com/event/earth-day-yoga-at-gallery-grow/
LOCATION:Gallery Grow Plant Bar\, 320 N Queen St.\, Lancaster\, Pennsylvania\, 17603\, United States
CATEGORIES:Classes and Workshops
